  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to test the feasibility and acceptability of internet-based Cognitive
      Behaviour Therapy (CBT) for persons diagnosed with bipolar disorder, type II. The idea is to
      treat residual depressive symptoms as well as using psychoeducation to improve their
      prognosis. Each participant will have a personal therapist that will provide guidance and
      support throughout the treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
